EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> are or probably should be a damage dealing class, what with the nukes and pets and such.  And, as I said, you seem pretty happy with your abilities and what you bring to groups and raids.<br><br>So far so good.<br><br>Now what if, and I am not claiming this is true mind you, but what if under some not terribly extreme circumstances or even common circumstance, the DPS of a pet alone turned out to be greater than comparable <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Paladin</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> DPS.  Assume, for the sake of this argument, that the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Mage + Pet</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> DPS figure looked okay before you knew what the breakdown was between Mage Nukes and Pet Melee.<br><br>Would this be an awful thing?<br><br>I am especially interested in your reasoning, and in particular any thoughts you have about the trade offs between utility and DPS.<br><br>Let me just say that I have been very impressed with what I have seen here, and with <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Paladins</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> defending their honor on other boards.<br><br>I only wish more classes could look within themselves, like <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Paladins</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> have, and see what they really bring to the table.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Razamatazz Pizzazz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Senior ArchMage, Ancient Fellowship, Xev<br><br>but originally...<br> <p><b>Balanz, son of Anz</b><BR><i>Paladin-Merchant of Kaladim</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uslitzjawbreaker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Slitz Jawbreaker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ding!!! - Email Mod for Custom Name</span><br>  Posts: 512<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/1/02 4:30:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.sho