tlords...<br><br>Mages CASTING should be much more powerful than a hybrids.  Hybrid melee is much more significant than a mages(pet).  DPS is not the be all and end all for Paladins by any means, but it is one of the major components.<br><br>Paladins do a quite lot of damage - if pet and mage both did the same damage as a Paladin, mage overall would be one of/the top damage dealers - by quite a long way at some levels.<br><br>If as you say overall DPS were fine, yet the pet were doing a lot of it, that implies that the mage himself is doing pretty weak damage.  I think a nuking mage should be putting out more damage than a Paladin... if not there are problems in pet unfriendly situations.<br><br>So overall a pet shouldn't outdamage a Paladin.  I think many people underestimate how much damage Paladins do, and also how important DPS is to Paladins.  I think a mage nuking should do a lot of damage, and the pet should boost that to make mage a top dmg dealer where pet is alive and doing it's full damage.  But always the mage casting should be the primary damage, IMO... <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwulf9.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wulf9</A> at: 4/1/02 6:16:42 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugallux.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gallux</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 125<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/1/02 5:30:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15113.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://members.optushome.com.au/mlorant/galluxtransparent.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=lef