ing.<br><br>I've seen a group of 4 magicians and 2 necros do some sick, sick things as a group. They've got 6 nukers and 6 half-tanks in the group while splitting the exp only 6 ways. If pet regen were reduced to that of a warrior (such that they had to be healed for all the damage they took rather than regenning) then the situation would not be so bad. However, a mage's epic pet can regen naturally from no health to full in a matter of a few minutes (not an hour like a warrior).<br><br>Harlan<br>Zebuxoruk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usenchy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Senchy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 344<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/1/02 8:12:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15113.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Class Balance Inquiry, Mage + Pet versus Paladin</span><hr size=1> I read you post a couple times just to see where you are coming from. This is what I think you are stating and asking.<br><br>On a raid/grin you state that a mage using spells and pet outdamages a paladin over time. The higher damage output of the mage is balanced with the ability of the paladin to heal/root park and buff. This makes them balanced against each other.<br><br>In a formula: &quot;mage DPS = pet DPS + mage spell cast DPS&quot;. <br><br>Now you are asking would it be a problem if the pet DPS portion of the equation is by itself greater than the paladin damage. <br><br>For an example, mage deals 80 DPS, paladin deals 55DPS. The mage's pet deals 60 DPS and the mage spells would only account for 20DPS. In that example the mages pet would deal more damage than the paladin.<br><br>So your question is if paladins would mind if the pet alone could outdamage the paladin. Casting damage by a mage would just add a little more damage on top.<br><br>Here's my answer:<br><br>Personally I would not care if your pet deals more damage by itself than me. I am fine with a mage dealing more DPS than a paladin, how you do that I could care less.<br><br>But I think you should care alot since the balance between pet damage and casting damage it very important for you.<br><br>For soloing, the pet needs to deal slightly less damage than you otherwise you will gain experience slower. The pet damage should though be very close to the casting damage otherwise you would constantly overaggro if you want to play the tighest and tank the mob vs your pet.<br><br>For raiding you want the pet damage to be low, otherwise your raid contributions where you are not allowed to use a pet become tiny.<br><br>If I was a mage then I would like my pet do as little damage as possible but enough to allow me to solo. That way I can contribute on raids the best above and beyond summoning mod rods.<br><br>Why do you want the mage pet do deal more damage than a paladin?<br><br> <p>Senchy Solariatus60 Crusader of Rodcet Nife55 Chanter of Rodcet Nife (Tymbor)Dol Amroth<BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=79641>My Profile</a><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usenchy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Senchy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 345<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/1/02 8:22:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15113.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Class Balance Inquiry, Mage + Pet versus Paladin</span><hr size=1> One issue I oversaw is that pet's regen health rather fast. <br><br>To stay balanced you really have to measure 